const faqs = [
  {
    q: "My commercial gas stove won't ignite on one burner. What's the most common cause?",
    a: "On gas commercial stoves, the most common cause is the igniter for that specific burner (year 4 to 7 typical wear), followed by the thermocouple proving the flame. About 50% of single-burner ignition failures are the igniter, 25% are the thermocouple, 15% are gas pressure issues, 10% are burner head clogs (grease and carbon buildup). We diagnose in that order and replace only the components that test as failed."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between commercial stove and commercial range repair?",
    a: "A commercial stove is a stovetop or cooktop only (burners on top, no oven below). A commercial range is the same burner deck with an oven beneath. Many operators use the terms interchangeably, especially when ordering equipment, and the burner-side service tree is largely the same across both. We service both. For range service (with oven), see our commercial range repair page. This page covers stovetop-only equipment: countertop hot plates, modular cooktops, drop-in cooktop sections."
  },
